  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Technical Assistance for Government Debt &amp; Infrastructure Finance - Brazil IFT 02. Government Debt and Infrastructure Finance - Brazil IFT 02</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Establish a stable and predictable macroeconomic environment that encourages the private sector to make productivity- and growth-enhancing investments. A solid macroeconomic foundation for growth consists of stable fiscal and monetary policies and institutions and the ability of the government to utilize such policies to productively influence the economy.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy, most importantly financial intermediation &#x2013; the efficient generation and allocation of savings to their most productive use.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This award strives to support the establishment of a sound private, well-functioning, equitable financial sector that fulfills critical roles in a market economy. More specifically, this includes The goal of this project is to increase private sector participation in the development, ownership, and financing of regional PPP/Concession infrastructure projects in Brazil and increasing the total amount of infrastructure spending to contribute to Brazil&apos;s economic development. Project components will include: 1) Enhancing the preparation of regional water infrastructure projects to attract private investment; 2) Standardizing the structure of concession contracts to increase private sector interest in infrastructure; 3) Broadening the counterparts&apos; knowledge of capital markets, and improving external communication; and 4) Improving the capacity to market projects to private investors.. Project is being scoped..</narrative>
  </description>
